"22 ounce bottle into chalice, bottled on 6/9/2014. Pours fairly crystal clear deep ruby/copper color with a 1 finger dense khaki head with great retention, that reduces to a small cap that lingers. Spotty soapy lacing clings on the glass, with some moderate streaming carbonation. Aromas of big raisin, plum, fig, pear, apple, light banana, clove, pepper, caramel, brown sugar, toast, spicy rye, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness. Damn nice aromas with good balance and complexity of fruity/spicy yeast, dark/bready malt, and earthy hop notes; with great strength. Taste of big raisin, plum, fig, pear, apple, light banana, clove, pepper, caramel, brown sugar, toast, spicy rye, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness. Good amount of earthy yeast/rye spiciness on the finish; with lingering notes of raisin, plum, fig, pear, apple, clove, pepper, caramel, brown sugar, toast, spicy rye, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness on the finish for a while. Damn nice complexity and balance of fruity/spicy yeast, dark/bready malt, and earthy hop flavors; with a great malt/yeast flavor balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a very smooth, crisp, and lightly slick/sticky mouthfeel that is great. Alcohol is very well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is an excellent specialty grain Quad style. All around great complexity and balance of fruity/spicy yeast, dark/bready malt, and earthy hops flavors; and very smooth and crisp to sip on for the ABV. The spicy rye-like triticale grain added a very nice amount of spiciness on the finish which I really liked. A very enjoyable offering."
