"Poured from a bomber into a snifter, the beer is a dark, vibrant, ruby-tinged, caramel coloring, with a thin, filmy, light, off-white head. Nose of old-world fruits (date, fig, and raisin), with a subtle spice blend of clove and nutmeg. Chocolate notes, too. Flavors are heavy fruit forward, with date and fig, and an herbal overtone, dark and grassy, along with solid spice profiles, and a hint of yeasty funk. Booze notes throughout, too. Solid brew. Full bodied, with a slight carbonation edge. Very balanced, with a building warmth into the richly sweet and spiced aftertaste. Smooth, slow, clean finish. Tasty beer."
