"Poured a reddish brown with virtually no head or lace and had an aroma that is typical of Belgian style beers; some sweet malts, yeast, dark fruits, touch of orange-like citric notes. Sticky, thick, slow sipping, there is a touch of booze in this beer. The yeast keeps it smooth and there is a mild sugary sweetness, pretty much caramel and maybe candi sugar, with some dark fruit flavors like fig and maybe raisin, and a touch of citric notes with orange and floral, clove spiciness. The triticale has no flavor presence in this beer, at least to me, although from other reviews this could be the floral spiciness I am getting. This beer isn't bad but it just seems to be a little messy and all over the place."
